  "text": "This study has several limitations. First, we did not include the analysis of physical activity. A recent study has shown that exercise reduces the risk of NAFLD and decreases liver enzymes, independent of obesity [CITATION_1] . Consistent with this study, low physical activity in NAFLD patients was also reported [CITATION_2] . Because physical activity is closely related to muscle mass, our findings might not be irrelevant, but the cross-sectional design of this study makes it difficult to infer causality between skeletal muscle, visceral fat, and FLD. Second, this study has selection bias because subjects were health check-up participants in a single center. Third, we used the BIA method to measure muscle mass. Though dual energy X-ray absorptiometry",
